        -:  380:/* ══════════════════════════ compiler thread ═══════════════════════════════ */
        -:  381:
        -:  382:/**
        -:  383: * Main loop of a background compiler thread.
        -:  384: *
        -:  385: * Dequeue strategy (zero-contention fast path, graceful fallback):
        -:  386: *   1. Try own queue first (only consumer — never contends with peers).
        -:  387: *   2. If empty, round-robin work-steal from each other thread's queue.
        -:  388: *   3. If all queues empty, block on the shared condvar.
        -:  389: *
        -:  390: * Stale-task detection:
        -:  391: *   entry->version > task.version_req  →  a newer compilation already happened;
        -:  392: *   discard and continue.
